Master Answer:
Consult your health care provider or visit a travel health clinic as early as possible, and preferably at least six weeks before you travel. This is important because some vaccines may take several weeks to become fully effective, and others may require more than one dose. Find out which vaccines may be recommended or required for your destination here.
Immunization Nurse
